The paper discusses the use of algorithms for autonomously discovering a set of useful options in Markov Decision Processes (MDPs). This topic is closely related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG), as it involves developing algorithms for decision-making. The paper also mentions simulation, which suggests that it may be relevant to robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the use of information theory tools suggests that the paper may also be relevant to information theory (cs.IT).
